{"title":"On Politics and Poetry","link":"https://kottke.org/24/07/on-politics-and-poetry","date":1721235732000,"content":"\n        <p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/songbird.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/songbird.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/songbird.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"867\" alt=\"a songbird perched on a branch\" /></p>\n\n<p>In order for me to write poetry that isn’t political<br />\nI must listen to the birds<br />\nand in order to hear the birds<br />\nthe warplanes must be silent.</p>\n\n<p>—<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/CqFjmVzpOYz/\">Marwan Makhoul</a></p>\n\n        \n\n         <p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/Marwan%20Makhoul\">Marwan Makhoul</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/poetry\">poetry</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/politics\">politics</a></p>\n\n        \n\n    ","author":"Jason Kottke","siteTitle":"Kottke","siteHash":"89a883271b4598f9b33ebe87be70d38557bcd266e68aee521a8f93622e0ab723","entryHash":"741c59f691d025a41d70879df7c9d6ea22f6b0dad035e590faedaaa18533b9a0","category":"default"}